  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will use a new &quot;H&quot; joystick for reduction on patients with femur fractures to
      investigate the reduction time, operating time and bone healing status for the evaluation of
      the clinical application benefits of this joystick.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study will design a new &quot;H&quot; joystick for reduction (which has received the national
      utility model patent) and will use this equipment on 80 patients (55 males, 25 females) with
      femur fractures to investigate the reduction time, operating time and bone healing status for
      the evaluation of the clinical application benefits of this joystick.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
